very, _very_ bad things happen. Types are namespaced (they get a package description that serves to avoid collisions) but method names do not. hence, java does not let you create type-esque constructs that let you refer to &#39;anything with an x method&#39;. Some languages do (this is called &#39;structural typing&#39;). Java is not one of those languages that lets you accidentally murder your friends when all you intended to do, was make a picture.

